{"id":33570,"title":"Guidelines of care for the management of atopic dermatitis: section 3. Management and treatment with phototherapy and systemic agents.","abstract":"Atopic dermatitis is a chronic, pruritic inflammatory dermatosis that affects up to 25% of children and 2% to 3% of adults. This guideline addresses important clinical questions that arise in atopic dermatitis management and care, providing recommendations based on the available evidence. In this third of 4 sections, treatment of atopic dermatitis with phototherapy and systemic immunomodulators, antimicrobials, and antihistamines is reviewed, including indications for use and the risk-benefit profile of each treatment option.","date":"2014-07-19","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24813298","annotations":[{"name":"Light therapy","weight":0.846603,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Light_therapy"},{"name":"Itch","weight":0.795167,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Itch"},{"name":"Inflammation","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inflammation"},{"name":"Chronic (medicine)","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronic_(medicine)"},{"name":"Histamine antagonist","weight":0.717091,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histamine_antagonist"},{"name":"Atopic dermatitis","weight":0.6638,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atopic_dermatitis"},{"name":"Antimicrobial","weight":0.655061,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antimicrobial"},{"name":"Cutaneous conditions","weight":0.551693,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cutaneous_conditions"},{"name":"Immunomodulation therapy","weight":0.492593,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunomodulation_therapy"},{"name":"Systemic disease","weight":0.485378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systemic_disease"},{"name":"Clinical trial","weight":0.472072,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_trial"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.459539,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Atopy","weight":0.280572,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atopy"},{"name":"Dermatitis","weight":0.214195,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dermatitis"},{"name":"Medical guideline","weight":0.0656404,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_guideline"},{"name":"Espionage","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Espionage"},{"name":"Section Three of the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Section_Three_of_the_Canadian_Charter_of_Rights_and_Freedoms"},{"name":"Option (finance)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Option_(finance)"},{"name":"Evidence","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evidence"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"}]}
